Donald, Kaymer Set Up Semifinal Meeting in World Match Play Golf

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-05-21T16:58:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-21/donald-kaymer-set-up-semifinal-meeting-in-world-match-play-golf.html
Luke Donald and  Martin Kaymer , the
second and third players in the Official World Golf Ranking,
advanced to a semifinal meeting at the Volvo World Match Play
Championship.  England’s Donald and Germany’s Kaymer both won their
quarterfinal matches by two holes, or 2-up, at the Finca
Cortesin Golf Club in Costa del Sol, Spain. Donald beat Masters
champion Charl Schwartzel of South Africa and Kaymer defeated
Alvaro Quiros of Spain.  The other semifinal will be between England’s  Ian Poulter 
and Belgian Nicolas Colsaerts. Poulter beat Italy’s Francesco
Molinari 2-up, while Colsaerts defeated U.S. Open champion
Graeme McDowell of Northern Ireland 2&1.  England’s Lee Westwood, the world’s No. 1-ranked golfer,
lost to Poulter in this morning’s round of 16. The semifinals
and final match will be played tomorrow.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  